    ## Use when
    - You must provide a heading to a region of a page. 
    - You must augment a section heading with additional contextual information or controls. 

    ## Visual style
    - Use the `eds-title__heading` and `eds-title__heading--level-*` helper classes to visually size the Title's heading text. See <eds-link eds-href="?tab=examples#heading-content">Size examples</eds-link>, and <eds-link eds-href="/visual-style/typography/typography.html#using-mixins-to-create-hierarchy">Designing with levels of hierarchy</eds-link>. 
    - Use `eds-border="top"` to aid in the visual delineation of page sections. 
    - Use `eds-border="bottom"` to add structure within a section that may include dense content or nested Titles. 

